      "span_text": "It has been proposed that CFTR functions as an internalizing receptor for P. aeruginosa, by binding of the outer core LPS of P. aeruginosa to amino acids 108-117 of CFTR; [CITATION_1] this suggests that CFTR has a direct and/or an indirect role in this process."
